reviews_data.review_text:
Very poor cup of coffee. Didn't like the mini creamers either. When I spend over $3 on a
Cup I want real quality cream

BEST COFFEE IN TOWN!!! We came to visit from out of town and this little spot was everything. From the service provided to the taste of their food and coffee. I highly recommend this establishment. Cant wait to visit again.

The iced black coffee was decent but unremarkable. While it was smooth and thankfully free of any acidity or burnt flavors, it lacked depth. There were no chocolate or nutty notes to add richness, leaving it somewhat flat in flavor. It's an acceptable choice for a simple caffeine fix but not one I'd seek out for a standout coffee experience.

Not coming back to this place. For $11 I order a large cappuccino with a cheese danish. What I got was a small cappuccino in a large cup with a cold cheese danish. It's theft! I want to support small businesses but not when they can't deliver. Sorry Cathy, but you lost me.

My friend and I recently entered Cathy's Coffee while we were waiting for my hair appointment and the owner was absolutely wonderful. She was extremely patient while we were figuring out what we wanted, and not to mention the food was phenomenal that we had to go back for more. I highly recommend this coffee shop.
Found my new local coffee spot!
Black female owned business with great coffee!

This quiet cafe is a gem in the rough. I ordered a cappuccino and cinnamon muffin which came to about $12 with a modest tip. I'd expect to pay around $14 at the most for coffee for two. Orders are done on the front counter (no kiosk), seating is plentiful and there's even a digital fireplace for a toasty get together! This quiet cafe feels like home though home also has a cortado on the menu;) (if I had to nitpick).

P.S. The owner is really genuine and makes you feel like family rather than a customer.

Coffee Conversation Community

Don't sleep on this cozy cafe!
I discovered this place randomly & wish I could have discovered it sooner ! The coffee is the great, clean and soothing atmosphere, it's really cute , and again the coffee is amazing.

This place is amazing, my wife and I went in for the first time today and the coffee was excellent. This will become our new coffee stop and strongly recommend it to anyone that loves a good cup of Joe
Fantastic coffee and snacks! Friendly staff and wonderful atmosphere. Will definitely be back again!
Great place to relax with your beverage of choice. Nice vibe. Friendly folks. Excellent brew.

Ran into this place because I moved into the area and it was a great atmosphere. They were professional and serious but also welcoming and engaging. No, i was not paid to write this and I don't know them personally. Genuine satisfied customer.

My husband and I had to go to Indian Trail and found this little coffee shop.  We love it!!! The coffee shop is very cozy and the coffee is so delicious, as well as the attention to the customer's needs. I am sure we'll be back again.  Stop by when you have a chance.
love this spot! yummie coffee and great egg frittatas! lots of seats to sit in- great owners!
Very nice coffee shop.

I spend 2-3 days a week here during lunch to get some remote work done. The atmosphere is very cozy and the coffee is fantastic unlike burnt roasts at Sbux. The owners are honestly some of the friendliest people you'll meet! If you haven't been here, you gotta give it a try!

I discovered this cute little coffee shop and the owners are so nice! The frittata, breakfast sandwiches, and coffee drinks are so good. It feels like home with how welcoming they are. Definitely stop in.

Such a welcoming atmosphere! The coffee is tasty with bountiful taste and the smoothie was so fresh. The male barista gave my nieces and nephews a FREE smoothie sample and he was so welcoming, alongside the beautiful owner who completed all the orders so gracefully and timely.   They were all so kind and loving. May Yeshua bless this business.
I thoroughly enjoyed the clean and quiet environment. The family environment was refreshing and reminds you of the joy of supporting your local businesses
Cathy is such a great host in her cozy cafe. I really enjoyed my visit and can't wait to go back!
Great, friendly staff. Good tasting coffee, reasonable prices. They have lounge and free wifi. Beautiful local place.
Cathy was so nice!! The cheese danish was so good & I loved the selection of coffee flavors  I had a raspberry iced latte.. delicious!

Walked in new customer.. i said a big hello and lady with grey hair behind counter just stood there.. when i explained i thought she was rude she said no im not like a child would respond..the  place has one person there i see why.. not friendly at all.. ill stick with alice jules they are top notch for sure

My husband and I discovered this little gem of a coffee shop about a month ago, and have been enjoying the wonderful service and products offered here. Gluten free, and dairy free, options are all available - and the GF muffins are fantastic. My favorite drink has become the Cascara Tea, and I highly recommend it. Cathy is a gem and we love spending our time here working or relaxing. We love supporting small, local businesses, as they often offer the best coffee and treats...and this shop doesn't disappoint!

: Captured here is a Cinnamon GF muffin and a Chai Spice tea with a hint of coconut milk.
enjoyed a stop in for a coffee and pastry service by Cathy herself!
Went here today again and the coffee brings me to life every time. I cannot find a coffee shop that is consistent every time, and is!!
Amazing coffee ! Fast service . Definitely check this place out
Cathy's is that wonderful neighborhood spot you can always rely on for a good cup of coffee and a nice book or study/work space. Her historical trivia board is possibly my favorite thing
This is a great small business! Its a great place to get some work done or just relax. It's roomy, well organized, comfy, the coffee is great, and the service is quick and reliable!

Great place for coffee, tea, etc. Music is 60's thru 90's and Golden Oldies. Great to meet for business and networking or just to have a little down time. Wi-fi is fast ! It's a place that vibes for the adult w/plenty to do !
Great coffee, very friendly
Been in here twice now and had great service and great coffee. Grew up in Indian Trail so it's nice to see a small business here. Locals are always great. Environment is great.

This place is overrated! They have Costco muffins and danish in the display case. The breakfast sandwiches were pre frozen Jimmy deans... I was Thrilled when I heard the microwave ding right before the lady came out with my sandwich...  Save your money and go to a gas station. The quality is the same.
First time, and I loved the coffee. Customer service was great, and helped me figure out what I wanted. Will definitely go back
EXCELLENT ROAST AND SERVICE WITH A SMILE .
I've been going to Cathy's for about 5 years. The coffee is great and Cathy's terrific. Plus the place is spotless!
Wonderful coffee. Good environment. Amazing service. A great place to stop and enjoy a coffee or tea.

I had a business meeting at Cathy's today and it was great! The atmosphere inside is relaxed. You can easily get work done, have a business meeting, or just grab coffee with a friend. They have all of the normal coffee options, plus muffins, cookies, and you can even order a breakfast sandwich. My Carmel latte was delicious!
Cute spot to hang out and has a yummy iced latte plus pumpkin muffins!

Coffee was extremely bitter. Along with the worker (owner?). She was very unpleasant. I could have ignored both, but after nastily telling my 16 month old son "don't tap the fish, it's a tv screen", (a fish tank scene was being played on a tv in place of where a fireplace would be), I decided I would never be coming back. She could have found a more polite way of asking me to please not have him touch it.
First time there. Coffee great. Pastry great. Great vibe and music perfect. Give it a try.

Cozy, warm atmosphere. I try to support local coffee shops whenever possible, and trust me, this place is worth skipping the Starbucks drive thru. I always receive great service, and the drinks are delicious
I tried some cascara tea and a gluten-free muffin. It was really good and a nice area to hang out and visit with a friend!
Amazing I love it here such a small cozy cafe! My dad ordered a coffee cooler 10/10 and I had a strawberry mango smoothie 100/10 and a gluten-free muffin 10/10.

Great local spot. Excellent coffee and nice ambiance with great service.
Highly recommend.

Cathy's coffee has great drinks, great service, and a small selection of food items. Come in and try your hand at a trivia question each day. Lots of space to sit to work and enjoy your coffee. Two small tables out front on a small walkway.
So so good, awesome service, awesome coffee, support local !
Nothing fancy, just a great spot for coffee with friends.  Move some chairs around and have a latte.!
We have been to nearly every coffee shop in the area, and Cathy's Coffee is certainly one of the best. The coffee shop is quiet and clean without a ton of frills, but the coffee is excellent.

Support Local Business!
Clean, inviting local coffee shop. Fresh bakery items, cold and hot beverage selections. My iced Chai was excellent and the cookie was very good and fresh.
The owner is often on premise and does a very good job of managing high quality beverages and doing so quickly.
When Covid concerns begin to fade, make this spot your go-to for morning coffee and afternoon meet ups.
I am NOT a friend of the owner, nor a family member. Having spent many years working in coffee retail I can vouch for the quality of the coffee and the expertise in the preparation. The unfavorable comments denigrating the coffee aren't accurate, or reflect a non-standard visit.
Recommended.
Cathy's Coffee is the absolute best! Come in  any day and stay warm by the digital fireplace , especially during this Good Friday.

We felt like something different, so my hubby found this coffee shop and we drove down from Cornelius to try it.  Cute building.  But the coffee was cold, and even when I asked for a warm up, the warm up was cold too.  Muffins and chili uninspired, but did like the quiche bites.

It's on a church campus, which is cool, but unless you're religious and want a dose of it with your coffee, skip it.  Wasp problem on the patio, so don't sit out there if you're allergic. Although it was freezing inside....

Also, owner not wearing a mask. We were disappointed.

Super cute coffee shop! I had the egg nog latte which was delicious. My hubs had a white chocolate peppermint latte which he said was like "Christmas in a cup". We'll be back again for sure! Check it out for yourselves!!!!
Great place for coffee & a sweet treat.
The best ever! The perfect place to visit with friends!
Best dirty chai latte in town!
Called Cathy's to inquire about purchasing whole bean coffee. Cathy was RUDE and full of ignorant sarcasm. Why? I will look elsewhere for coffee!
Wonderful coffee and fabulous service

The BEST coffee shop in Charlotte area.
Cozy interior, delicious drinks, and always amazing service.

Support local (ESPECIALLY when it really is the better option)!
Always on point!
Amazing Coffee, amazing service! Cathy was super pleasant! Will definitely be coming back here again!
Great dark roast coffee!
Great atmosphere. Good coffee
I love Cathy's Coffee. She is great. She makes me an awesome vanilla chai tea icey drink. Great place to gather
Friendly, homey vibe.  Coffee was tasty!

Delicious pastries and coffee.   Nice little place in Indian Trail.   I really wish they had later hours especially during the week and we're open on Sunday.   Sometimes after work I like to grab a snack and usually don't get home until after 3.
Great coffee and nice attention

Cathy's Coffee Is one of my favorite places to go. It is nestled right in the heart of South Matthews/Indian Trail. Cathy has a fun trivia board each day to earn a discount on your purchase, AMAZING quality coffee and confections (highly recommend the blueberry muffins).
They also will experiment with you! Interested in trying a new flavor combination? Cathy is all in. Even though I haven't been there in a while, she greets me by name every time and it makes my day!

Super Friendly staff, really cool "market" on Saturday but iced-coffee was just okay.  It tasted like regular coffee, brewed as regular hot coffee, and put in the fridge.  If you're into cold brew then you'll notice the difference.
Super quick, Priced right, the place looks great, and the owner is super friendly. I will definitely come back again!
Cathy's is awesome! Shes got good coffee and gluten free bakery items that are delish and even celiac friendly. Love everything about it!
Amazing little hidden gem! Loved the comfy couches in the back and the huge helpings of bakery items.
Delicious coffee. Great place for a meeting, or to work outside the office.
Nice place for a cup of coffee with friends or just for work

Besides having the best coffee around there are so many o ther things to like about Cathy's coffee.
They also have teas and fruit smoothies,  pastries, muffins, egg sandwiches, amazing quiche and oatmea...l perfect for a quick breakfast or you can hang out and enjoy.
That's the best thing about Cathy's...plenty of space to spread out &  do your thing, meet people, or ust hang out with the locals.
Everything you could want is at Cathy's that's why it's my favorite place!

I went to the place with my daughter in order  to support local business and regreted almost immediately. Not only we were not even greeted but we were rushed and treated in a very demeaning manner. We had smiles on our faces when we walked in but the owner and her helper interrupted us in an angry tone when we were trying to ask questions about vegan options for my daughter. What a disappointment. There was not even a line so We weren't holding anyone up. We planned on having a nice morning together but those women really turned is off. I do not recommend going there.
Nice place with awesome coffee
Good little shop. Decent selection. Ok prices.
Great coffee and even better people!
Great quiet little place with very competitive prices and good coffee. I'll take this over Starbucks any day.

Cathy's is great coffee, and Cathy herself is super.  She seems to know many folks drink orders before they make it to the counter, and this is a great place to relax, have a drink, and get a bit of work done.  Highly recommend!

Cathy's Coffee is a great little one-off cafe with lovely decor, excellent coffee and tea served in real mugs, and a variety of fresh pastries.  My only regret is that there are no evening hours at all and Saturday is only 9am-noon.
Great vibe, WiFi, and yummy pumpkin chi's.
Love Cathy's Coffee. Very clean and inviting. Your conversation space is respected. Coffee is always fresh and served with Love.
I went here for the first time today and the coffee was amazing! I will definitely go back!
A nice little coffee house with very good coffee. Enjoyable atmosphere and free Wi-Fi.
First time coming in yesterday. Cathy was wonderful and accommodating to my dietary restrictions! I look forward to seeing her again and trying more things at this coffee shop!

I love this place! Went there for the first time last week and haven't stop wanting to go in! Best iced coffee I've had. The ladies there are so nice and it make the experience even better! Sadly they close at 3 so I can't go after school! I would high recommend Cathy's coffee!

i love this place so much! The lady to always take my order remembers and greets me every time, asking me about school, my job, etc etc. she makes the experience so good, not to mention the delicious iced coffee with irish cream flavoring! I just wish she would stay open one more hour so i can come after school :( highly recommend this place, so good!
Charming local coffee shop with delicious coffee

Visited the coffee shop this morning for the first time ever. Was greeted by Cathy herself what a nice lady. Got a regular coffee and a chocolate muffin. Very nice place with great service and coffee/pastries. Will be back again.
Very nice, non-corporate coffee place. Fast internet, fine coffee, pleasant atmosphere and service. Excellent value compared to "Big S". You need to try this place!
Very good coffee
Great atmosphere
Great little local coffee shop.  The owner was very friendly and welcoming! My cinnamon chai tea latte was amazing!  I will definitely be going back.
Great place to enjoy a cup of coffee. Feels like a home setting with a friendly staff.
Such a friendly and cozy environment. Coffee and pastries are amazing!
Enjoyed Saturday morning coffee with some great people!
Great atmosphere, great coffee, super kind lady, free wifi. What more could you want?
The best! Great coffee, great atmosphere, great people.

Great coffee, clean shop, owner was very friendly to me.  My only complaint, the hours of operations.  I wish the shop stayed open a little later.  Other than, it's worth going and enjoying a great cup of coffee.
Supper cute coffee shop and great coffee. Thank you!
Pretty good coffee. Hate that it closes at 3 pm.
Really bad customer service! They aren't welcoming at all. I would not recommend going there.
Iced mocha with peppermint. Yum!  Everything here is so good, and the owner Cathy is so friendly. Great place to sit for a while.
This is my favorite place to relax and enjoy a good cup of coffee. Bob Johnston

I would like to say the owner Cathy is one of the rudest people I have ever met. I walk in and introduce myself to her, in hopes that I can get a business donation towards the Sun Valley High School Student Council. After I tell her why I am here and all about what we do she responds with "let me think about it.... ummmm NO". I was embarrassed and yes I am a kid but no one should ever be treated so rudely.
Charming Cofree shop. Owner Cathy is so nice and personal. Cofree is the best!
Great coffee and delicious snacks, very comfy interior.
Greeeeaaaat place to relax and enjoy your coffee! Very friendly atmosphere.
Pleasant atmosphere, locally-owned, great quality and good prices.  Lots of homemade items.  Very nice owner.
Love this place. My favorite coffee shop. Great atmosphere, great coffee and baked goods.

This has turned into one of my favorite local hot spots. I'm a Starbucks lover, but after going to Cathy's Coffee I'm hooked. Cathy offers several delicious latte options for vegans and lactose intolerant. My favorite is a soy latte. When I'm up for a treat, I'll add a pump of pumpkin spice syrup. Cathy also has yummy home baked goods  from a local baker. The mini coffee crumb cakes and almond poppy seed muffins are to die for. What ever  your coffee or tea desires are, you'll be sure to find it at Cathy's Coffee.
great cozy friendly ambiance

Cathy's is a great coffee shop for anything you would need a coffee shop for. Meetings, reading a book, connecting with friends. Cathy works hard as the sole owner and employee and is excellent with customer service, knowing her customers well.

Four stars because I have found the wifi speed to be pretty low compared to other coffee places I've visited and they close at 3, which is a bummer - would love a late night coffee shop but I understand the business might not be there.

If you're near here, you should come by. She'll take good care of you!
Cute. Quaint. Good coffee.
Great coffee and environment. Not too loud and not to quite. One of my favorites!
great atmosphere, clean, friendly
I enjoy the herbal teas and the almonds!
Cathy's is strategically located between two of my employers. So naturally, it's my go-to place to unwind or to get in some wi-fi time!! Cathy is so friendly and helpful!!

Discovered this place thru a networking event and absolutely LOVE it! Great cozy atmosphere and the owners are really nice...... not to mention the coffee is delicious. If you're in the mood for a special treat try the nutella flavored coffee!
